sentences: Maya Shipman (born August 16, 1987), better known by her stage name 'Suzi Analogue', is an American recording artist, musician, and songwriter based in New York City.
In 2012, Suzi Analogue and Tokimonsta collaborated and released an EP under the Moniker "Analogue Monsta ".
In 2013, she launched her own record label, Never Normal Records.
Her first project released on the Never Normal label "CHILLS + THRILLS" was named Best Cassette Of 2014 by UK's FACT Magazine.

She performed a live set on Boiler Room for the Teklife release of DJ Earl's "Open Your Eyes" album, which she also collaborated on which went on to be named in the 20 Best Electronic Albums Of 2016 by Pitchfork.
